# JavaScript Coding Style

This rule file defines JavaScript coding style and conventions.

## File Patterns
- `app/javascript/**/*.js`: JavaScript files
- `app/javascript/controllers/**/*.js`: Stimulus controllers

## Hotwire Conventions
- Use Turbo Drive for page transitions
- Use Turbo Frames for partial page updates
- Use Turbo Streams for real-time updates
- Use data-turbo attributes for fine-grained control
- Follow progressive enhancement principles
- Handle Turbo events appropriately
- Use proper caching strategies

## Stimulus Conventions
- Use Stimulus only for interactive UI elements
- Keep controllers small and focused
- Use data-controller for controller attachment
- Use data-action for event handling
- Use data-target for element references
- Use data-value for state management
- Use lifecycle callbacks appropriately
- Follow naming conventions for controllers and actions

## JavaScript Best Practices
- Avoid jQuery or other heavy libraries
- Use ES6+ features when available
- Use const and let appropriately
- Use arrow functions for callbacks
- Use async/await for asynchronous code
- Use proper error handling
- Keep code modular and reusable
- Follow the principle of least power

## Testing
- Test Stimulus controllers
- Test Turbo interactions
- Test JavaScript modules
- Use proper test helpers
- Test both success and failure cases

